.TH "TODOPRO EDIT" "1" "2026-02-27" "1.0.0" "todopro edit Manual"
.SH NAME
todopro\-edit \- Edit a task interactively or via flags.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B todopro edit
[OPTIONS] TASK_ID
.SH DESCRIPTION
Edit a task interactively or via flags.
.PP
If no flags are given, launches an interactive prompt showing current
values so you can edit each field in turn (press Enter to keep).
.PP
Examples:
  tp edit 3f --content "New title" --due tomorrow
  tp edit 3f --priority 3
  tp edit 3f          # interactive
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-c,\fP \-\-content TEXT
New task content
.TP
\fB\-\-description\fP TEXT
New description
.TP
\fB\-d,\fP \-\-due TEXT
New due date (e.g. 'tomorrow', '2026-03-01 14:00')
.TP
\fB\-p,\fP \-\-priority INTEGER
New priority (1=low, 2=medium, 3=high, 4=urgent)
.TP
\fB\-\-project\fP TEXT
New project (name or ID, fuzzy search supported)
.TP
\fB\-o,\fP \-\-output TEXT
Output format  [default: pretty]
.TP
\fB\-\-json\fP
Output as JSON (alias for --output json)
